Put the @British pork mince{600%g} in a #mixing bowl{}. Cut the roots off the @spring onion{3} and chop them in half, separating the green from the white parts. Finely slice both the green and white parts and keep them separate.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one) and separate the @coriander{1} leaves from their stalks. Chop the coriander stalks as small as you can and roughly chop the leaves.

Add your coriander stalks, the white parts of the spring onion, the garlic, the @ground coriander{1}(tsp) and half the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp} to the bowl containing the mince, and mix well. Shape the mince mix into four even-sized meatballs per person.

Tip: Make sure the meatballs are well shaped to stop them falling apart as they cook.

Put the @basmati rice{350%g} in a #pot{} with the @star anise{2} and a @salt{pinch}. Pour in the @water{700%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, pop on a #lid{}, reduce the heat to low and simmer for ~{10%minutes}. After 10 mins, remove from the heat and leave the rice to finish cooking in its own steam for a further ~{10%minutes}.

Cut the @red onion{2} in half through the root, peel and then slice into thin half moon shapes. Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and finely slice.

Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium heat and add a splash of @oil{}. Fry your meatballs for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side until golden brown. Transfer your meatballs to a #plate{}, you will finish cooking them in the curry later.

Cook the onion and pepper in the same pan you used for your meatballs, for ~{5%minutes} or until soft. Add half of the @red Thai style paste{1} and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Tip: Add more or less curry paste depending on how much you like spice!

Pour in the @coconut milk{800%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and add your meatballs to your curry. Cook your curry for ~{10%minutes} or until your meatballs are no longer pink in the middle. Stir in the @baby spinach{1%bag} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Tip: Taste the curry and if you want more heat, add more of the red curry paste and cook for another minute.

Finish your curry with the rest of the soy sauce and the juice of half the @lime{1}. Serve your curry with your fragrant rice and a final sprinkle of your remaining coriander and the green parts of your spring onion.